f=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=169.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Ambassador's daughter picks up a sword</span><hr size=1> “A bear that can speak.” Natori muttered to herself, even as she felt the healing magic flow through her, “I must have hit my head harder than I thought.” <br>
<br>
Out loud, she called out to him, “What manner of magic is this, an animal that speaks, healing magics that don’t do their work instantly?”<br>
<br>
The bear let out a deep rumbling laugh, “I come from a land far from here, where the ice never melts, and the ground beneath never sees the light of day.  As for the fur,” The bear waved his arms in almost a manlike fashion, and before her stood one of a race she’d only heard about, “Tis but an illusion.”<br>
<br>
Natori wrinkled her nose, “You looked better as a bear.”<br>
<br>
Again, that laugh, “Now, about my proposal?” the man asked as he reverted to the animalistic form.<br>
<br>
“I don’t like you, but for now we share a common enemy.  You kill the more seasoned, I keep the novices off of you so they don’t interrupt your magic, you get their grass necklaces and I keep any of the skullcaps we might find? It sounds to simple.”<br>
<br>
“Oh it won’t be that simple child, that I promise you.  These buggers are tough as me mom’s jerky.  What do you need all of those skullcaps for anyway?”<br>
<br>
“I was promised a better weapon if I proved myself by killing these creatures.  Their skullcaps are the proof that I’ve sent them to their maker, or to mine.” Why she was after the particular weapon that was reward for this task was none of the bear’s business.  This was Natori’s culling task, the task given her to prove herself worthy of a place amongst those of the Violent Harvest.<br>
<br>
<br>
“Well let’s kill us some midgets why don’t we.” With that, the bear hurled into action against one of the halflings.   One of the novices began trying to distract the behemoth with magic.  Natori took a slice at him with her sword, and drew him away from the others so that she might remove his head from his shoulders without interference.  No skullcap.  10 more went down like the first, and in that time, only 1 had worn a skullcap.<br>
<br>
It was then that Darkrayne returned from his trip to High Pass.  A messenger informed her that he was looking for her and that she was to meet him at the bank.  It had been a long time since she’d met the one left in charge of her care.  She wondered what he would think of her now that she was no longer a weakling child barely able to step on a spiderling.  (((**** OOC****  More to come, I write far less often than I game, so my writing’s well behind my actually progress here   *****OOC******)))<br>
